Is `asscalar()` missing here? Is using NDArray actually faster thank numpy array? This comparison converts a ndarray to a scalar. In my experience using a python list is fastest, followed by numpy array, followed by ndarray. We can convert the list to mxnet ndarray after the O(N) preprocessing. 
You can try a distribution with 1M classes to compare the speed. 
