@kaxil Thank you for clarifying.  I was operating under the assumption that `airflow.apache.org` was set as a `CNAME` to `airflow.readthedocs.io` using the domain setting on Read the Docs (https://readthedocs.org/dashboard/airflow/domains/).  Is this something that's been considered?

Is the longterm plan to keep the separate Apache site?  For instance, suppose we have 2 LTS releases like 1.10 and 2.0, would the Apache site then serve both versions with the version dropdown?

The reference example I'm thinking of is how Django hosts all versions on one site - https://docs.djangoproject.com/ (try bottom right version button).

