It's tough to do an implementation of "undefined" behavior without, well, defining it -- which is I suppose the argument in favor of "skeleton"/"util" vs a "standard" tracer.  Append is the more common denominator, I've switched back to that, but I'm guessing this is a pretty short half-life file.

> we could have a super-simple polyglot standalone "OpenTracing" tracer service
@bensigelman I like that idea, was thinking about the same thing with the name "basic tracer" or similar.  Low on bells and whistles to emphasize core duties.

